				<BR><B>History, experience and competence: </B>While we are the manufacturer for standard tooling balls sold by distributors, we are <B>now in our 34th year</B> of tackling the challenge of precision tooling balls. Call outs for tooling balls are not made casually; the engineer has a reason. We have earned the trust of hundreds of firms in commercial, military and other government industry/aviation.
				<BR><BR>
				<FONT SIZE="5" COLOR="">Why One-Piece?</FONT>
				<BR><B>Stability: </B>Tooling balls take a lot of pressure; you want one solid piece of steel, not a welded assembly that can break, warp or mis-align at the seam.
				<Br><B>Concentricity: </B>Only a one-piece construction lends itself to high tolerance and consistency in concentrity. You just can't get this result with a welded assembly.
				<BR>
